1
00:01:22,182 --> 00:01:25,583
Help

2
00:02:42,128 --> 00:02:43,459
Nothing

3
00:02:44,931 --> 00:02:49,300
''Did he call?
- No, he came while you were asleep''

4
00:02:49,602 --> 00:02:52,298
''He was going to the club,
he'll be back late''

5
00:05:30,096 --> 00:05:32,360
When did you come?
Are you all right?

6
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:40,097
Why do you do this to me?
- What did l do? l came for you

7
00:05:40,540 --> 00:05:46,342
You were asleep. What's the matter?
- You know l hate seeing you with Anita

8
00:05:49,115 --> 00:05:51,276
What do l lack in?
What do seek in Anita?

9
00:05:51,784 --> 00:05:55,117
Anita and her husband are
my business partners

10
00:05:55,288 --> 00:06:01,716
ls kissing necessary in business?
- We cracked a good deal

11
00:06:01,994 --> 00:06:04,861
''Just celebrating, what's wrong?''

12
00:06:06,132 --> 00:06:10,660
Such an old-fashioned outlook.
- Your father liked my outlook...

13
00:06:10,937 --> 00:06:14,873
when he came to see me in Mumbai.
And you too. What did you see in me?

14
00:06:16,476 --> 00:06:19,934
A pretty woman who was working
for an art gallery

15
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:22,471
Someone who was interacting
with intelligent folks

16
00:06:23,149 --> 00:06:25,140
l took you for one of those girls
who move with the times

17
00:06:25,485 --> 00:06:28,318
We're standing in the 21st century.
l want to take you ahead

18
00:06:28,488 --> 00:06:30,547
And you're holding me back?
Why don't you change

19
00:06:32,825 --> 00:06:38,821
''lf it strengthens our relationship,
l'm willing. But not a change...''

20
00:06:38,998 --> 00:06:43,094
that brings us to shame before
each other. l can't become Anita

21
00:07:05,124 --> 00:07:07,115
l love this place

22
00:07:13,132 --> 00:07:15,123
l love you very much

23
00:07:17,136 --> 00:07:19,127
Very much

24
00:07:20,740 --> 00:07:24,141
And l love my independence
just as much

25
00:07:30,983 --> 00:07:34,077
That's why l stay far away
from my father

26
00:07:35,087 --> 00:07:39,581
Why don't you understand Vaidehi?
Just understand. Then you won't mind

27
00:07:43,095 --> 00:07:45,086
Let go.
- l'm your husband

28
00:07:45,431 --> 00:07:48,093
You didn't think of that when
you were kissing Anita?

29
00:07:48,668 --> 00:07:52,331
Forget Anita. l'm not in love
with Anita. l'm in love with you

30
00:07:52,505 --> 00:07:56,339
''What was that? Lust? Love one,
lust for someone else?''

31
00:07:56,509 --> 00:07:58,500
''Someone at home,
someone outside?''

32
00:08:04,517 --> 00:08:06,109
Let go

33
00:08:06,452 --> 00:08:07,783
Leave me

34
00:08:14,126 --> 00:08:15,457
''Raghu, leave me''

35
00:08:50,530 --> 00:08:54,591
''l may be your husband's family
doctor. But to me, you're a sister''

36
00:08:55,568 --> 00:08:58,162
''When you called me to say that
you have a fever, l felt...''

37
00:08:58,271 --> 00:09:00,330
''from the tone of your voice,
something else is bothering you''

38
00:09:00,573 --> 00:09:02,837
That's why l asked you to see me
here instead of coming to the clinic

39
00:09:03,175 --> 00:09:05,166
To let you talk your heart out
to your brother

40
00:09:06,913 --> 00:09:09,905
Just give me a prescription
for an ache and a fever

41
00:09:10,349 --> 00:09:13,512
l've informed the nurse.
Go down to the clinic

42
00:09:13,686 --> 00:09:17,622
Take an injection and leave blood
and urine samples for testing

43
00:09:18,524 --> 00:09:22,517
''But tell me, do your parents know
that Raghu assaults you?''

44
00:09:23,062 --> 00:09:24,461
No

45
00:09:25,197 --> 00:09:28,928
Hurry up! l've chosen a fur coat
for you. The shop will close down

46
00:09:29,201 --> 00:09:31,135
l don't want it?
- Don't want it? l select...

47
00:09:31,237 --> 00:09:34,468
''a 40,000 dollar furcoat for you
and you say you don't want it?''

48
00:09:36,542 --> 00:09:41,138
''Nice dresses, expensive jewellery,
big homes, London-America''

49
00:09:41,747 --> 00:09:45,547
That's what parents look for when
they give their daughters away

50
00:09:46,152 --> 00:09:49,144
But is that all a woman expects
from her husband?

51
00:09:49,488 --> 00:09:52,150
''What else? Poverty, suffering?''

52
00:09:53,826 --> 00:09:57,057
''Must you always talk in riddles?
Anyway, pack some woollens''

53
00:09:57,163 --> 00:10:00,496
lt'll be cold where we're going.
- l've packed for you

54
00:10:01,434 --> 00:10:03,425
l'm talking about you.
- l'm not coming

55
00:10:06,472 --> 00:10:08,133
Over and over again!
Never happy

56
00:10:09,508 --> 00:10:12,500
''When he was a child of ten,
his mother passed away''

57
00:10:13,579 --> 00:10:16,412
''Grew up in boarding school, became
stubborn. Been like this ever since''

58
00:10:16,582 --> 00:10:21,178
Just like his father.
Your mother-in-law too...

59
00:10:21,287 --> 00:10:23,414
found it difficult when she came
to America for the first time...

60
00:10:23,522 --> 00:10:29,358
after getting married.
But she adapted to my lifestyle

61
00:10:30,863 --> 00:10:33,354
''You too will adapt, and Raghu will
get to understand you''

62
00:10:33,799 --> 00:10:40,136
Once he begins to understand that
l'm human. He thinks l'm a machine

63
00:10:41,140 --> 00:10:47,136
''Like his car, to drive anywhere,
anytime, at will''

64
00:10:48,147 --> 00:10:50,945
He ignores my feelings

65
00:10:54,153 --> 00:10:59,489
''Minor incidents. Happen. You are
Raghu's wife, the honour of our family''

66
00:10:59,825 --> 00:11:01,816
You will carry the lineage forth

67
00:11:04,163 --> 00:11:07,428
''lf you don't accompany him,
people will talk''

68
00:11:07,967 --> 00:11:11,164
lt's important that you
accompany him and you shall

69
00:11:16,108 --> 00:11:23,514
''Lost in love...''

70
00:11:25,518 --> 00:11:31,388
''he's benumbed''

71
00:11:33,726 --> 00:11:41,132
''l pine for him...''

72
00:11:42,068 --> 00:11:48,132
''he's unaffected''

73
00:12:27,046 --> 00:12:28,411
''Come''

74
00:12:28,581 --> 00:12:30,674
''Come to me''

75
00:12:30,850 --> 00:12:35,116
''Oh come to me''

76
00:12:46,198 --> 00:12:53,798
''Don't make me pine like this''

77
00:14:09,148 --> 00:14:11,309
''Why is the fire so chilling?''

78
00:14:11,550 --> 00:14:13,814
''Why is pain so sweet?''

79
00:14:14,053 --> 00:14:16,146
''Why are stars so mischievous?''

80
00:14:16,388 --> 00:14:17,377
''Tell me''

81
00:14:21,160 --> 00:14:25,620
''Why is the breath so hot?
Why are these lips so soft?''

82
00:14:25,898 --> 00:14:28,332
''Touch me, my love''

83
00:14:28,934 --> 00:14:29,866
''Tell me''

84
00:14:34,106 --> 00:14:35,835
''My tousled tresses...''

85
00:14:36,108 --> 00:14:38,099
''caress''

86
00:14:38,444 --> 00:14:42,437
''Don't spurn me, my love''

87
00:14:43,749 --> 00:14:45,114
''Take...''

88
00:14:45,451 --> 00:14:47,282
''take away...''

89
00:14:47,453 --> 00:14:52,117
''take may heart away''

90
00:14:53,325 --> 00:15:01,130
''Don't make me thirst''

91
00:15:54,853 --> 00:15:56,844
''Someone's thirsting...''

92
00:15:57,122 --> 00:15:59,113
''with hopes in the heart...''

93
00:15:59,458 --> 00:16:02,120
''looking for a lover...''

94
00:16:02,294 --> 00:16:03,625
''my love''

95
00:16:06,999 --> 00:16:09,126
''ln midnights' past...''

96
00:16:09,301 --> 00:16:11,462
''we'll talk...''

97
00:16:11,737 --> 00:16:14,137
''when every moment,
l have...''

98
00:16:14,306 --> 00:16:15,637
''my love''

99
00:16:19,545 --> 00:16:21,945
''This love...''

100
00:16:22,147 --> 00:16:24,138
''do not spurn''

101
00:16:24,350 --> 00:16:26,147
''My love...''

102
00:16:26,385 --> 00:16:28,319
''give me one bright moment''

103
00:16:29,154 --> 00:16:31,088
''Don't...''

104
00:16:31,256 --> 00:16:32,951
''make me so pensive''

105
00:16:39,098 --> 00:16:45,435
''Don't leave me aching''

106
00:16:52,978 --> 00:16:54,969
''Come''

107
00:16:55,214 --> 00:16:57,114
''Come to me''

108
00:16:57,316 --> 00:17:01,912
''Oh come to me''

109
00:17:03,122 --> 00:17:10,119
''Don't make me pine like this''

110
00:17:33,585 --> 00:17:37,578
Raghu and Anita know
how to live it up

111
00:17:39,091 --> 00:17:43,494
You don't mind your wife with
my husband? Like this...?

112
00:17:44,563 --> 00:17:51,765
l love my wife dearly. lf l mind it
if she's happy in Raghu's company...

113
00:17:51,970 --> 00:17:59,103
''what love would that be? l say,
forget religion. Join me''

114
00:17:59,545 --> 00:18:01,979
''We too could, like Raghu and Anita...''

115
00:18:27,139 --> 00:18:28,936
''Where are you going, Vaidehi?''

116
00:18:30,375 --> 00:18:33,538
What is the matter?
- Let's go home

117
00:18:34,313 --> 00:18:36,144
And desert my own party?

118
00:18:39,485 --> 00:18:42,147
''l don't like this crowd,
with people like Rahul and Anita''

119
00:18:42,488 --> 00:18:44,922
What problem do you have with Rahul?
- He was suggesting

120
00:18:45,157 --> 00:18:49,150
Just like you go around
with his wife...

121
00:18:51,430 --> 00:18:53,159
l too...

122
00:18:53,499 --> 00:18:55,160
''could, with him''

123
00:19:00,606 --> 00:19:04,042
''When he said whatever he said,
he was in his senses''

124
00:19:04,276 --> 00:19:07,609
''Whatever he might say, nothing's
happening without your consent''

125
00:19:11,083 --> 00:19:12,744
My consent?

126
00:19:15,187 --> 00:19:17,178
You have no objections?

127
00:19:18,190 --> 00:19:22,183
Your friend! Someone who ought to
consider me his sister-in-law...

128
00:19:22,461 --> 00:19:25,692
''speaks to me in this mien,
and you have no objections?''

129
00:19:26,198 --> 00:19:29,634
Every man wants to have
a relationship with a pretty woman

130
00:19:30,135 --> 00:19:33,298
''You're exotic. He gave it a try,
he failed''

131
00:19:34,006 --> 00:19:37,942
''Sure, l'm old-fashioned. But...''

132
00:19:38,143 --> 00:19:42,375
''your outlook is filthy, despicable!
- Let's discuss outlook later''

133
00:19:42,481 --> 00:19:44,676
Everyone's waiting.
- l'm not going anywhere with you

134
00:19:52,958 --> 00:19:54,949
What face will l have left if
l stand out there all alone?

135
00:19:56,295 --> 00:19:59,492
l'm not going anywhere near
folks like Rahul and Anita

136
00:19:59,898 --> 00:20:03,732
We've invited Rahul and Anita.
How can l throw them out?

137
00:20:03,835 --> 00:20:05,166
That's up to you

138
00:20:08,173 --> 00:20:10,164
l'm not going

139
00:20:18,850 --> 00:20:21,978
''Over every little issue,
you try to blackmail me?''

140
00:20:23,455 --> 00:20:25,184
Twenty first century!

141
00:20:31,463 --> 00:20:33,124
Regret you will

142
00:20:35,067 --> 00:20:38,400
No place in my home for someone
who doesn't care for my prestige

143
00:20:56,154 --> 00:20:58,554
Mr Raghu has asked you
to return to lndia

144
00:20:59,491 --> 00:21:02,324
His father doesn't wish
to discuss this with you

145
00:21:02,828 --> 00:21:04,159
Please come

146
00:21:55,147 --> 00:21:56,944
How is Raghu?

147
00:21:58,150 --> 00:22:00,846
Out of danger. But...
- What...?

148
00:22:01,019 --> 00:22:02,384
ls he married?
- Yes

149
00:22:02,487 --> 00:22:04,478
Any children?
- Not yet

150
00:22:06,391 --> 00:22:10,157
He might lead a normal married life.
But he will never become a father

151
00:22:17,469 --> 00:22:20,165
You should not have returned.
- ls this not my home?

152
00:22:20,339 --> 00:22:23,399
''No, once married, the woman's home
is her husband's home''

153
00:22:27,846 --> 00:22:29,609
Your Daddy is right

154
00:22:30,115 --> 00:22:35,576
''The home a woman enters after marriage,
she ought to leave only in death''

155
00:22:35,854 --> 00:22:38,914
''She's troubled as it were, and you...
- Shut up Pinky''

156
00:22:40,125 --> 00:22:42,855
''Had your sister cared for you,
she wouldn't have returned like this''

157
00:22:44,863 --> 00:22:51,132
Who will marry you after this?
- People will point fingers

158
00:22:51,570 --> 00:22:59,375
They will talk. You must go back.
The honour of our family...

159
00:22:59,478 --> 00:23:02,936
is in your hands.
- As also your husband's honour

160
00:23:04,149 --> 00:23:09,143
''l understand. ln every family, it's
the woman who shoulders the honour''

161
00:23:09,321 --> 00:23:11,312
But the woman has no honour

162
00:23:16,395 --> 00:23:21,162
''Such a vast property, and
l have no heir after Raghu''

163
00:23:21,600 --> 00:23:24,160
What are you saying?
Your daughter-in-law is pregnant

164
00:23:25,504 --> 00:23:28,166
Vaidehi is pregnant?

165
00:23:29,174 --> 00:23:33,440
l tested her blood and urine.
You didn't see the report?

166
00:23:33,879 --> 00:23:35,779
l don't see Vaidehi.
Where is she?

167
00:23:35,881 --> 00:23:38,577
Have you called Vaidehi?
- No

168
00:23:39,317 --> 00:23:41,308
Why haven't you called her?
- Why should l call her?

169
00:23:42,120 --> 00:23:46,113
Won't you inform her about
your accident?

170
00:23:47,125 --> 00:23:52,654
Forget it Dad. She doesn't care for me.
Why tell her about my accident?

171
00:23:53,131 --> 00:24:00,594
''Don't talk like that, son. Call her up.
- lt's over between us''

172
00:24:03,475 --> 00:24:06,137
She's your wife. Don't you talk
like that of her

173
00:24:09,548 --> 00:24:11,539
Vaidehi isn't returning

174
00:24:12,150 --> 00:24:14,675
''l'll marry ten times over,
if that's what you want''

175
00:24:14,853 --> 00:24:18,482
But not an heir.
Only Vaidehi can deliver that

176
00:24:31,102 --> 00:24:39,635
''l didn't want to tell you this way,
but doctors say, you can't father''

177
00:24:47,385 --> 00:24:52,322
''Son, l've just come to know that
Vaidehi is pregnant''

178
00:24:54,025 --> 00:24:59,691
''She's carrying your child. That's
why l suggested, you call her over''

179
00:25:01,366 --> 00:25:04,130
Save our family from extinction

180
00:25:08,206 --> 00:25:13,701
''Let her have the baby. Once we have
our child, and if she insists...''

181
00:25:13,812 --> 00:25:18,579
''on disobeying her, divorce her.
Marry again. Live as you like''

182
00:25:19,150 --> 00:25:23,143
Who's stopping you? lf she raises
a hue and cry over the child...

183
00:25:23,255 --> 00:25:25,155
we can have her bumped off

184
00:25:51,116 --> 00:25:55,849
''Raghu my boy! Yes, l'm fine son.
How are you? Bless you, son''

185
00:25:56,187 --> 00:25:59,122
''Yes Vaidehi is here, right here.
One minute''

186
00:26:02,127 --> 00:26:04,118
Raghu is calling. Come on

187
00:26:10,802 --> 00:26:13,930
''Vaidehi, l know you're cross,
very cross''

188
00:26:14,539 --> 00:26:17,133
''l've made you suffer,
and God has punished me''

189
00:26:18,143 --> 00:26:19,940
l met with an accident

190
00:26:20,478 --> 00:26:22,810
What...? When...?

191
00:26:24,149 --> 00:26:26,743
''Are you all right?
- Yes, l'm alive''

192
00:26:27,819 --> 00:26:31,880
All by dint of your virtuosity

193
00:26:38,096 --> 00:26:39,825
l'm coming

194
00:26:41,099 --> 00:26:42,088
Tomorrow

195
00:26:42,267 --> 00:26:44,258
Tomorrow...?
- Yes tomorrow

196
00:26:45,437 --> 00:26:49,100
l've organised everything.
My manager in Mumbai will escort you

197
00:27:02,721 --> 00:27:04,382
She's coming

198
00:27:10,495 --> 00:27:12,053
Send Vaidehi over with Fakhruddin.
Tomorrow

199
00:27:12,197 --> 00:27:15,564
''Fakhruddin is an idiot, and he
has never been abroad''

200
00:27:16,134 --> 00:27:19,262
Send him. She will enjoy
Fakhruddin's company

201
00:27:19,371 --> 00:27:20,702
That's important

202
00:27:27,045 --> 00:27:28,808
Why are you crying?

203
00:27:29,147 --> 00:27:31,274
''Fakhru, don't go away''

204
00:27:31,816 --> 00:27:33,681
Don't leave us

205
00:27:34,085 --> 00:27:36,417
''Shut up! l'm not leaving
this world, am l?''

206
00:27:36,821 --> 00:27:38,812
''For the first time, l'm going
abroad! To America!''

207
00:27:39,024 --> 00:27:40,889
Send me off with a smile.
Crying...?

208
00:27:43,094 --> 00:27:46,086
What's it?
- lt's a long journey to America

209
00:27:46,931 --> 00:27:52,267
''How will you travel alone?
- l'm flying, not walking''

210
00:27:52,804 --> 00:27:54,101
Shut up!

211
00:27:55,106 --> 00:27:56,767
My baby...

212
00:27:59,110 --> 00:28:00,634
''Bless you, son''

213
00:28:02,647 --> 00:28:09,109
''Whom are you leaving me with?
- Salma dear, don't overact. Shut up''

214
00:28:09,287 --> 00:28:15,920
''Fakhru my son, mark my words, never
break a woman's heart''

215
00:28:16,394 --> 00:28:23,300
''Ominous is a woman's curse.
- Sure mother, l'll be back''

216
00:28:25,136 --> 00:28:31,939
''My baby, my sweet boy!''

217
00:28:32,143 --> 00:28:36,136
l'll miss my plane. l'll buy you
a shopful of sweets when l return

218
00:28:37,148 --> 00:28:38,479
Farewell

219
00:28:43,154 --> 00:28:47,147
This is scared vermilion.
Have Raghu put it on you

220
00:28:54,499 --> 00:28:55,966
Be happy

221
00:28:59,037 --> 00:29:03,167
Just remember that he means
everything to you

222
00:29:04,509 --> 00:29:07,842
That's your home. Not this

223
00:29:11,182 --> 00:29:13,173
''Come, my child''

224
00:29:19,357 --> 00:29:21,848
Where's the New York check-in counter?
- New York check-in counter?

225
00:29:21,960 --> 00:29:22,949
Yes

226
00:29:26,197 --> 00:29:28,529
Looking for a platform?
Worked the railways before this?

227
00:29:34,639 --> 00:29:38,473
''Vaidehi, where are you calling from?
- Airport, Mumbai''

228
00:29:38,643 --> 00:29:41,134
''l'm coming to New York.
- No, don't come here now''

229
00:29:42,147 --> 00:29:46,743
Why...?
- You tested positive

230
00:29:47,018 --> 00:29:48,576
You're pregnant

231
00:29:52,490 --> 00:29:56,153
''Have you told Raghu?
- Yes, and now it has become...''

232
00:29:56,261 --> 00:30:00,163
''a big problem for you.
- What are you saying, doctor?''

233
00:30:02,066 --> 00:30:05,593
''After the accident, we've come to know
that Raghu can never father a child''

234
00:30:06,070 --> 00:30:10,837
Raghu and his father want
your baby for an heir

235
00:30:11,910 --> 00:30:14,970
That's why they are calling you.
They are very powerful

236
00:30:15,079 --> 00:30:16,842
They can do anything here

237
00:30:18,383 --> 00:30:23,184
''What am l to do, doctor?
- Take my advice. Don't come here''

238
00:30:23,421 --> 00:30:26,515
And don't take any steps before
you consult a good lawyer over there

239
00:30:36,334 --> 00:30:39,132
Have you had a chat with the boss?
- Yes

240
00:30:42,040 --> 00:30:45,806
Shall we? lt's time for the flight.
- Sister-in-law! Congratulate me!

241
00:30:46,144 --> 00:30:48,305
l've just seen an international
boarding card for the first time

242
00:30:48,513 --> 00:30:51,141
Now no one's stopping me
from going to America

243
00:30:52,150 --> 00:30:54,414
l'm feeling sick.
l can't go today

244
00:30:55,153 --> 00:31:00,147
''No, we must. lt's time for the flight.
- No, l'll go later''

245
00:31:01,059 --> 00:31:05,155
No problem. Just relax. l'll go over
and tell Mr Raghu

246
00:31:06,164 --> 00:31:08,962
Quiet! l'm going over.
l'll explain to the boss

247
00:31:09,167 --> 00:31:12,728
''Fakhru, you are accompanying the lady.
Please come. Boss' orders''

248
00:31:13,037 --> 00:31:14,834
We'll put a doctor on the flight

249
00:31:17,175 --> 00:31:19,166
Let me use the washroom

250
00:31:21,179 --> 00:31:23,170
''Fakhru, get a wheelchair''

251
00:31:55,580 --> 00:31:57,411
This baby is mine

252
00:31:59,150 --> 00:32:01,141
l have a right to it

253
00:32:03,488 --> 00:32:05,649
l'm not giving this baby to anyone

254
00:32:07,492 --> 00:32:09,153
Never

255
00:32:10,061 --> 00:32:12,689
What do l do? Where do l go?

256
00:32:13,698 --> 00:32:16,030
''Once married, the woman's home
is her husband's home''

257
00:32:18,169 --> 00:32:20,660
''No place in my home for someone
who doesn't care for my prestige''

258
00:32:22,974 --> 00:32:27,172
''Raghu and his father want
your baby for an heir''

259
00:32:41,459 --> 00:32:43,927
''Has Vaidehi boarded the plane?
- No sir, she...''

260
00:32:44,128 --> 00:32:46,119
''Why not?
- She spoke you, didn't she?''

261
00:32:46,464 --> 00:32:49,797
l didn't speak to her.
- But she did speak to someone

262
00:32:50,435 --> 00:32:53,734
''Then she suddenly says she's unwell,
and she'll go after a couple of days''

263
00:32:54,038 --> 00:32:56,370
''l'm reasoning with her,
but she isn't willing''

264
00:32:56,607 --> 00:32:59,804
Where is she?
- ln the toilets. l'm waiting outside

265
00:33:01,412 --> 00:33:03,403
lt's the ladies'

266
00:33:08,152 --> 00:33:09,949
''Come on, sit''

267
00:33:10,321 --> 00:33:14,155
''Fakhru, this isn't for me.
Go to the ladies' toilet''

268
00:33:17,061 --> 00:33:19,495
l respect you for being my superior.
But you needn't dictate...

269
00:33:19,597 --> 00:33:23,158
my toilet-using habits. Why Ladies?
l'll use the Gents

270
00:33:24,168 --> 00:33:27,501
We only got to see whether
madam is in there or not

271
00:33:50,361 --> 00:33:52,124
Let the truck leave

272
00:33:57,668 --> 00:34:00,466
The lady is making trouble.
The boss is going on calling

273
00:34:00,571 --> 00:34:04,132
l don't know what to do...
- Forget her! l fell because of you

274
00:34:06,577 --> 00:34:09,512
Have you seen a woman hereabouts?
- You call her a lady

275
00:34:10,148 --> 00:34:12,480
Have you seen the lady?
We're travelling to New York

276
00:34:13,651 --> 00:34:17,553
Have you seen a woman in blue?
- Not here

277
00:34:18,022 --> 00:34:21,014
Have you seen any vehicles leave?
- Our trucks just left for Nagpur

278
00:34:21,225 --> 00:34:22,817
Carrying oranges?
- No

279
00:34:22,994 --> 00:34:24,325
''l see, they bring oranges from there''

280
00:34:30,001 --> 00:34:32,993
''Give the phone to Vaidehi.
- Sir, we're looking for him''

281
00:34:35,206 --> 00:34:40,337
We came to the cargo section
looking for her. Seems that...

282
00:34:40,445 --> 00:34:44,575
some trucks just left for Nagpur.
She might've taken one of them

283
00:34:46,117 --> 00:34:47,914
Go to Nagpur right away

284
00:34:50,688 --> 00:34:52,121
l'm coming to lndia

285
00:34:53,124 --> 00:34:56,116
What did he say?
- We're going to Nagpur

286
00:34:57,128 --> 00:34:59,119
Go on. l'll carry the information
to New York

287
00:35:01,432 --> 00:35:05,129
Nagpur is 26 hours away.
New York is 16 hours. l'll be back

288
00:35:05,937 --> 00:35:07,928
l'm not doing ajob
that takes me to Nagpur

289
00:35:08,339 --> 00:35:09,465
Coming

290
00:35:34,332 --> 00:35:36,095
''On which road...''

291
00:35:36,267 --> 00:35:38,098
''to which city...''

292
00:35:38,402 --> 00:35:41,394
''are you going?''

293
00:35:42,473 --> 00:35:46,102
''Gazing into the distance...''

294
00:35:46,677 --> 00:35:49,578
''with tired eyes;
home is far away''

295
00:35:51,115 --> 00:35:52,707
''Lonely...''

296
00:35:53,117 --> 00:35:54,744
''moments...''

297
00:35:55,119 --> 00:35:58,384
''after leaving the caravan...''

298
00:35:58,923 --> 00:36:00,914
''on which road...''

299
00:36:01,125 --> 00:36:02,854
''to which city...''

300
00:36:03,127 --> 00:36:05,721
''am l headed?''

301
00:36:16,474 --> 00:36:20,137
''Officer, check each
and every vehicle''

302
00:36:20,411 --> 00:36:21,935
Unload them

303
00:36:22,146 --> 00:36:26,549
Stop staring at me. Tell your
constables to get to work

304
00:36:26,951 --> 00:36:28,816
We must find the lady

305
00:36:29,153 --> 00:36:31,246
Forget the horses.
Find the lady

306
00:36:31,622 --> 00:36:36,491
''Check all the trucks, down to the
last one. l repeat, search it''

307
00:36:40,097 --> 00:36:42,088
Can't l board another flight
on this card?

308
00:36:42,266 --> 00:36:44,894
No.
- Then what to do with this?

309
00:36:52,777 --> 00:36:54,608
There she is

310
00:37:04,121 --> 00:37:05,850
She's running away

311
00:37:43,828 --> 00:37:45,819
''Not to fear. l'm not the police,
l'm a thief''

312
00:37:47,098 --> 00:37:53,298
What are you trying to get away with?
- Nothing stolen. l'm trying to save...

313
00:37:53,437 --> 00:37:55,268
what's mine

314
00:38:05,516 --> 00:38:07,780
''Not to worry. He's alive,
just knocked out''

315
00:38:07,918 --> 00:38:09,510
Half a biscuit knocked him out

316
00:38:11,122 --> 00:38:12,919
My special biscuit

317
00:38:14,125 --> 00:38:15,615
Laced

318
00:38:16,127 --> 00:38:18,721
Cost-effective and reliable.
By the time you're halfway through...

319
00:38:18,829 --> 00:38:21,127
you're asleep. My Biscuit Number One

320
00:38:23,134 --> 00:38:24,624
You got a pin?

321
00:38:27,138 --> 00:38:28,537
Yes

322
00:38:32,476 --> 00:38:37,140
''He's a colleague. l steal by night,
he steals by day''

323
00:38:39,150 --> 00:38:41,141
Wonderful! Opened up

324
00:38:42,153 --> 00:38:44,144
Your pin just worked a wonder

325
00:38:52,363 --> 00:38:55,491
''All of 50,000! Makes my life''

326
00:39:00,838 --> 00:39:03,432
You get a cut. Ten percent.
Keep five thousand

327
00:39:05,176 --> 00:39:08,168
Hire charges for your pin. Keep it.
- No! l'm not taking this

328
00:39:08,412 --> 00:39:11,506
''Then l'll owe you a favour,
and l hate that''

329
00:39:11,982 --> 00:39:13,973
''No, l'm not taking.
- Take it, please''

330
00:39:14,518 --> 00:39:16,179
Open each and every shop. Check.

331
00:39:16,420 --> 00:39:18,718
My boss is connected right up
to the prime minister

332
00:39:18,889 --> 00:39:20,186
Come with me

333
00:39:23,527 --> 00:39:27,520
l'll run. l'll divert their attention.
You just have to walk out

334
00:39:28,999 --> 00:39:30,933
''We owe each other nothing,
score settled''

335
00:40:25,689 --> 00:40:28,180
You... here...?
- l'm looking for a girl

336
00:40:44,475 --> 00:40:46,807
This is another policeman.
He won't recognise you

337
00:40:48,145 --> 00:40:51,478
''He's a freeloader. He'll eat,
take a tip and leave''

338
00:40:53,484 --> 00:40:58,478
''At weddings, thieves sneak in too.
No, l'm just doing time-pass here''

339
00:40:58,956 --> 00:41:01,151
''Hello, Aunt.
- Bless you son''

340
00:41:02,059 --> 00:41:05,153
Are you staring at my coat?
lt's two-in-one

341
00:41:05,629 --> 00:41:08,325
Black inside for black deed.
Social checks out here

342
00:41:08,532 --> 00:41:12,969
''Would you like a cold drink?
Hey, won't you offer the lady a drink?''

343
00:41:14,171 --> 00:41:18,335
''At weddings, cold drinks are fun.
Everyone having a good time?''

344
00:41:18,642 --> 00:41:23,341
A relative's wedding?
- l don't believe in relationships

345
00:41:24,081 --> 00:41:26,606
''l got an appointment at two.
Until then, time-pass''

346
00:41:27,084 --> 00:41:29,177
''And to keep suspicions at bay,
a bit of conversation''

347
00:41:29,587 --> 00:41:31,851
We're still the same
we were. Strangers

348
00:41:33,023 --> 00:41:35,457
''How did you know who's from the boy's
family, and who's from the girl's?''

349
00:41:36,026 --> 00:41:38,688
''Simple. Those going around
with folded hands, bowing...''

350
00:41:38,796 --> 00:41:42,288
are from the girl's family.
The proud ones belong to the boy's

351
00:41:43,033 --> 00:41:45,126
You don't believe? Take a look

352
00:41:49,573 --> 00:41:54,135
l can even tell you who
the girl's father is

353
00:41:55,045 --> 00:41:57,138
Tell me.
- The fellow with a drooping moustache

354
00:41:57,615 --> 00:42:00,015
The peak of his urban is askew
like a cock's crown

355
00:42:00,417 --> 00:42:02,408
And he sports a smile despite being
as helpless as a sacrificial goat...

356
00:42:02,620 --> 00:42:08,820
and goes around apologising
to everyone is the bride's father

357
00:42:09,493 --> 00:42:13,827
''Forgive me, the journey must've
been tiresome. Burt what could l do?''

358
00:42:14,164 --> 00:42:16,394
l booked the hall right besides
Sudama Hall near the railway station

359
00:42:16,567 --> 00:42:20,560
Sudama Hall? Sounds so depressing.
What might it be like?

360
00:42:21,171 --> 00:42:26,006
''No, the venue was fine. But
the bridegroom's father insisted...''

361
00:42:26,110 --> 00:42:31,343
on Laxmibai Hall. lt cost me thrice
as much. But l'm satisfied

362
00:42:31,515 --> 00:42:36,919
This place is grand! The bride's room
is grand. And the bridegroom's...

363
00:42:37,121 --> 00:42:40,784
Want to know who
the bridegroom's father is? Ask me

364
00:42:41,525 --> 00:42:46,792
Tell me.
- His whiskers point at 11:05 am

365
00:42:47,464 --> 00:42:52,527
''He wears a turban poised like a snake,
and he's chesting out at 45 inches''

366
00:42:53,037 --> 00:42:55,403
''He's strutting about as if he's
constipated, and if...''

367
00:42:55,539 --> 00:42:58,667
''he's threatening people over everything,
then he's the bridegroom's father''

368
00:42:59,810 --> 00:43:01,072
There

369
00:43:01,245 --> 00:43:05,147
Shall we leave the wedding?
- Forgive me

370
00:43:05,316 --> 00:43:08,479
The chairs have been organised.
- Why didn't you order...

371
00:43:09,153 --> 00:43:14,489
''a few hundred more beforehand?
Look, my guests are standing''

372
00:43:15,159 --> 00:43:20,324
''Forgive me, you gave me a list of
500 guests. l ordered 700 chairs''

373
00:43:20,965 --> 00:43:23,490
Looks like some more have arrived.
- You expect them to get their chairs?

374
00:43:24,635 --> 00:43:27,502
''Tell me, you expect them to bring
their food along too?''

375
00:43:27,905 --> 00:43:31,341
Please do not say that...
- lf you can't afford as little...

376
00:43:31,442 --> 00:43:33,433
why did you enter into
an alliance with us?

377
00:43:33,844 --> 00:43:36,369
''No dearth of girls for my son,
was there, Damodar?''

378
00:43:36,547 --> 00:43:39,448
Yes brother-in-law...?
- Any dearth of girls for my son?

379
00:43:39,717 --> 00:43:44,450
Not at all. There was a long queue!
Each better than the other

380
00:43:44,622 --> 00:43:46,613
And their fathers were rich!
- Heard that?

381
00:43:46,790 --> 00:43:48,348
''Say, do we leave?
- Shall we...?''

382
00:43:48,459 --> 00:43:52,452
''Excuse me, the chairs are coming.
Let me see''

383
00:43:52,663 --> 00:43:54,130
Why aren't the chairs here yet?

384
00:43:55,466 --> 00:44:00,130
l guess l'm in the right place!
ls this a wedding?

385
00:44:00,471 --> 00:44:05,465
''No, they're mourning their dead.
- Wrong venue again''

386
00:44:06,143 --> 00:44:13,311
''Nekchand makes me run all over town!
Where do l find you, Nekchand?''

387
00:44:13,584 --> 00:44:17,577
''Hey, where are you off to?
- To find my friend Nekchand''

388
00:44:18,155 --> 00:44:21,955
''Hey, that's you Nekchand!
- Lay the chairs. You're late''

389
00:44:22,426 --> 00:44:24,360
People are leaving.
- Leaving...?

390
00:44:24,962 --> 00:44:26,953
ls the bridegroom's father
Mr Hazarilal?

391
00:44:27,164 --> 00:44:29,064
''He is, and how many times
do l tell you that?''

392
00:44:29,166 --> 00:44:33,102
l know all about him! He has deserted
weddings twice already

393
00:44:33,270 --> 00:44:36,262
''l'm not letting him do it again,
don't you worry''

394
00:44:36,440 --> 00:44:41,537
l'll have his guests glued to their
chairs. Anyone who gets up is dead

395
00:44:43,113 --> 00:44:46,549
The bridespeople must behave.
- Who the hell are bridespeople?

396
00:44:46,684 --> 00:44:49,312
We're the bridespeople.
- Bridespeople? Are we...?

397
00:44:49,453 --> 00:44:51,444
Yes.
- Then l'll behave myself

398
00:44:55,125 --> 00:44:56,922
This is for Mr Damodar

399
00:44:57,461 --> 00:44:59,452
Brother...
- Yes sister?

400
00:45:00,364 --> 00:45:02,662
This is for you.
- For me?

401
00:45:03,133 --> 00:45:06,660
Oh l forgot your maidservant's name...
- You mean Basanti?

402
00:45:07,471 --> 00:45:09,132
''Yes...
- Basanti, take this''

403
00:45:09,406 --> 00:45:13,137
And this is for you.
Two sarees and a shawl

404
00:45:13,844 --> 00:45:15,835
May l take a look?
- Certainly. Please see

405
00:45:16,146 --> 00:45:19,138
l selected them personally. For you.
- l see

406
00:45:25,055 --> 00:45:27,148
That's bronzed silk. From Benares

407
00:45:28,158 --> 00:45:31,958
Not by the looks of it. l only wear
Kanjivaram silks

408
00:45:33,097 --> 00:45:37,090
''Basanti, keep these for yourself.
And the shawl too''

409
00:45:37,801 --> 00:45:40,793
''Your father works as a nightwatchman,
right? lt'll be useful for him''

410
00:45:43,307 --> 00:45:46,299
Being put to good use.
- Why of course...

411
00:45:46,510 --> 00:45:49,707
l'll buy another pair for you.
Nice ones

412
00:45:52,015 --> 00:45:56,111
''You're too hesitant. Eat.
- No, you go on''

413
00:45:56,520 --> 00:45:58,511
''ln the first place,
let's get informal''

414
00:45:58,789 --> 00:46:01,451
''And eat, enjoy, like everyone else''

415
00:46:05,129 --> 00:46:08,121
You think all these people are here
to bless the couple?

416
00:46:09,466 --> 00:46:13,129
''Everyone has a purpose to be here.
Look, over there''

417
00:46:13,637 --> 00:46:16,834
l don't want this rotten suit!
And also return your saree

418
00:46:16,940 --> 00:46:18,737
We're leaving.
- Why should l leave?

419
00:46:18,876 --> 00:46:21,140
l like the saree. You leave
if you want to

420
00:46:21,378 --> 00:46:24,040
You'll ditch your husband
for a saree?

421
00:46:25,382 --> 00:46:27,441
You're insulting me!
- Goodness!

422
00:46:34,224 --> 00:46:36,089
What happened?
- What's the matter with her?

423
00:46:36,293 --> 00:46:38,887
l don't know. Suddenly...
- Fetch a glass of water

424
00:46:38,996 --> 00:46:40,554
l'll take care of her

425
00:46:42,099 --> 00:46:45,091
''Drink up, you'll feel fine.
- Shall l take her to a doctor?''

426
00:46:45,269 --> 00:46:48,500
She doesn't need a doctor.
She isn't sick

427
00:46:49,540 --> 00:46:53,533
''One minute, aren't you Bansidhar's son?''

428
00:46:55,112 --> 00:46:57,774
The one who runs the flour mill

429
00:46:59,116 --> 00:47:03,450
''l tell myself, why does he look
so familiar?''

430
00:47:04,121 --> 00:47:10,458
''Like father, like son. Careless.
The poor thing is pregnant''

431
00:47:10,794 --> 00:47:13,592
''And he drags her here,
makes her stand in a crowd''

432
00:47:14,131 --> 00:47:18,295
Let her be comfortable.
Give her the goodies

433
00:47:19,136 --> 00:47:21,127
''Of all the father's duties,
do some at least''

434
00:47:21,572 --> 00:47:23,130
Moron

435
00:47:25,409 --> 00:47:31,075
''l'm sorry, because of me...
- Never mind. But in this condition...''

436
00:47:32,683 --> 00:47:39,486
Does your husband know you're carrying?
- Yes. That's why l'm here

437
00:47:52,436 --> 00:47:56,099
l read somewhere that cigarette smoke
is injurious for babies

438
00:47:56,340 --> 00:47:57,671
Let me get you some fruit

439
00:48:00,444 --> 00:48:01,775
Forgive me

440
00:48:02,112 --> 00:48:07,106
''Why are you apologising to me?
l'm your wife. Well, what's up?''

441
00:48:07,384 --> 00:48:11,787
''Got to dish out another 20,000 for
the reception. Get me the cash. Quick''

442
00:48:12,122 --> 00:48:15,114
''No way! We've already spent 20,000
out of the amount for the dowry''

443
00:48:16,126 --> 00:48:22,463
What are you doing? Wasting money?
Refuse him. Don't touch the dowry

444
00:48:23,133 --> 00:48:25,124
That devil warned you at the outset.
He will walk out...

445
00:48:25,235 --> 00:48:27,396
''if he isn't given 500,000 before
the conclusion of the wedding''

446
00:48:27,537 --> 00:48:29,528
There's a lot of time to go
for the conclusion of the wedding

447
00:48:29,740 --> 00:48:32,140
''lf he isn't given 20,000
he'll walk out right now''

448
00:48:32,342 --> 00:48:35,937
''Let him walk.
- Saroj, listen! Give me 20,000''

449
00:48:36,146 --> 00:48:39,411
l'll make good the shortfall.
l'm borrowing from someone. Hurry

450
00:48:39,583 --> 00:48:43,815
l'm not going to spare you!
l've conned the whole world

451
00:48:44,054 --> 00:48:47,956
You don't get away with conning me!
No sparing you!

452
00:48:48,158 --> 00:48:50,752
Forgive me...
- No sparing you!

453
00:48:50,961 --> 00:48:54,158
''l'll find him, somewhere l will!
No sparing you!''

454
00:48:56,033 --> 00:48:58,024
ls it organised?
- lt will be organised

455
00:48:58,368 --> 00:49:03,829
Will be organised? Not organised yet?
- You could say it's nearly organised

456
00:49:04,074 --> 00:49:09,171
You better get one thing clearly.
The money should be in my hands...

457
00:49:09,279 --> 00:49:12,510
exactly at quarter to five.
Only then the wedding is concluded

458
00:49:12,716 --> 00:49:17,176
''Else, we're leaving. We're walking out.
- Why are you joking?''

459
00:49:17,621 --> 00:49:24,993
l am not joking. Perhaps you don't know
that l walked out twice before

460
00:49:25,696 --> 00:49:28,995
My father walked out thrice.
You understand?

461
00:49:29,199 --> 00:49:31,133
Yes.
- How much did l say?

462
00:49:31,301 --> 00:49:33,132
500000
- ln...?

463
00:49:33,303 --> 00:49:34,964
Cash.
- ln currencies of...

464
00:49:35,138 --> 00:49:36,537
Five hundreds.
- Brilliant

465
00:49:38,475 --> 00:49:41,376
Make sure you eat coconut.
My mother used to say...

466
00:49:41,545 --> 00:49:46,141
eating coconut gives you fair babies.
You eat too. Your son will be fair

467
00:49:46,316 --> 00:49:48,944
What if it's a daughter?
- Eat even more coconut

468
00:49:49,152 --> 00:49:53,384
''ln this country, the ugliest of men
look for the fairest of brides''

469
00:49:57,027 --> 00:50:03,159
Wonderful! What a lovely gathering!
- That's what worries me

470
00:50:03,500 --> 00:50:06,333
What...?
- Maybe you haven't provided for so many

471
00:50:06,970 --> 00:50:10,838
But don't you water down the curries.

472
00:50:11,174 --> 00:50:14,507
''lf you do, we leave.
The lovely gathering vanishes''

473
00:50:16,179 --> 00:50:18,977
You're lucky to be watching
my last performance

474
00:50:19,649 --> 00:50:24,177
''ln a while, l'll be collecting
my passport, visa and air ticket''

475
00:50:24,354 --> 00:50:26,720
''a friend is giving me ajob in Dubai.
Tomorrow morning, l'm in Mumbai''

476
00:50:26,857 --> 00:50:32,124
The evening flight takes me to Dubai.
And l'll try never to return

477
00:50:34,965 --> 00:50:36,956
Forgive me! Thank God the bottles
didn't break

478
00:50:37,134 --> 00:50:39,932
The bridegroom's friends ordered it.
- You...?

479
00:50:40,137 --> 00:50:42,128
l'm Bansidhar's son.
- Who's Bansidhar?

480
00:50:42,305 --> 00:50:44,933
''The flour miller.
- Hey, you're one of us!''

481
00:50:45,142 --> 00:50:47,406
Will you please deliver it?
- l'll be back

482
00:50:48,412 --> 00:50:52,405
Bansidhar's son? Grow so tall
in six months?

483
00:50:52,949 --> 00:50:55,474
Greetings.
- Bansidhar's daughter-in-law?

484
00:50:55,986 --> 00:50:58,477
Bless you. Now where was l going...?

485
00:51:00,157 --> 00:51:05,959
Same song. Boring.
- You've sung it twice already

486
00:51:06,496 --> 00:51:10,159
l'll sing it over and over again!
- You're creating a scene

487
00:51:10,500 --> 00:51:15,961
Will you mar my wedding?
- What to do friend? l'm ruined

488
00:51:16,173 --> 00:51:20,405
What happened? Tell me.
- No! lf l speak...

489
00:51:20,510 --> 00:51:26,312
the skies will be rent asunder!
The earth will weep! May l have a drink?

490
00:51:26,450 --> 00:51:30,784
No! Booze is over.
- Here's as much as you want

491
00:51:31,021 --> 00:51:33,785
Why did you have to walk in now?
- You should've come earlier

492
00:51:34,024 --> 00:51:36,117
l just found out you're short of beer.
- Who are you?

493
00:51:36,460 --> 00:51:38,792
Bansidhar's son.
- Bansidhar...?

494
00:51:39,129 --> 00:51:43,395
Flour miller. What's your problem?
- My friend is drunk

495
00:51:43,867 --> 00:51:46,392
l hope he doesn't create a scene.
- What's his name?

496
00:51:46,570 --> 00:51:48,128
Gulshan

497
00:51:48,472 --> 00:51:50,463
''You take care of this,
l'll take care of him''

498
00:51:51,141 --> 00:51:58,013
Friend is friend no more.
- Why are you getting so emotional?

499
00:51:58,215 --> 00:52:03,482
''The girl l was in love with,
is going to my friend''

500
00:52:04,955 --> 00:52:09,153
She has betrayed you?
- Not exactly

501
00:52:09,426 --> 00:52:16,161
She didn't know l was in love with her.
- Your friend stabbed you in the back?

502
00:52:18,168 --> 00:52:23,504
Not exactly. He didn't know
that l fell on the sword

503
00:52:23,974 --> 00:52:25,498
What's your problem?

504
00:52:28,178 --> 00:52:29,907
''How are you, my child?''

505
00:52:30,213 --> 00:52:31,908
Have you eaten?
- Yes

506
00:52:33,116 --> 00:52:35,914
Where's your husband?
- Oh let me tell you...

507
00:52:36,019 --> 00:52:38,852
Say what? You're getting bored
sitting alone

508
00:52:39,022 --> 00:52:41,456
Take this and come with me
to the bride's room

509
00:52:41,691 --> 00:52:43,682
You're looking so pretty

510
00:52:45,295 --> 00:52:47,695
''What's going on?
- Look aunt, she's so pretty''

511
00:52:47,964 --> 00:52:52,128
Oh l'm glad! Our bride looks
so pretty

512
00:52:54,037 --> 00:52:58,633
''This is Nekchand's daughter, Maithili.
And she's... what's your name my child?''

513
00:52:59,042 --> 00:53:00,304
Vaidehi

514
00:53:00,477 --> 00:53:05,141
What a wonderful coincidence!
Two girls named after Sita together!

515
00:53:05,482 --> 00:53:07,143
She's Vaidehi...
- Oh yes! And l'm Maithili

516
00:53:07,484 --> 00:53:09,475
Both named after Sita

517
00:53:09,819 --> 00:53:13,311
Hello sister! Never met you before.
- She's Bansidhar's daughter-in-law

518
00:53:13,490 --> 00:53:16,152
Bansidhar who...?
- The flour miller

519
00:53:16,359 --> 00:53:24,562
Girls! Listen. Take good care of her.
Keep feeding her. She's pregnant

520
00:53:28,038 --> 00:53:29,938
''What do you want? Boy or girl?
- Boy, of course''

521
00:53:30,106 --> 00:53:33,269
''Shut up! Let me ask her.
- No, we do the asking''

522
00:53:33,543 --> 00:53:37,536
No! Who's getting married?
You get to ask at your wedding

523
00:53:37,681 --> 00:53:39,342
l get to ask her today

524
00:53:40,116 --> 00:53:43,449
Why can't we ask her?
- Just because you're the bride?

525
00:53:43,954 --> 00:53:49,449
Yes. Today's my day.
- Only today. After the wedding...

526
00:53:49,559 --> 00:53:53,461
the days and nights will be his.
- That's just what l want

527
00:53:54,130 --> 00:54:00,126
''Come on girls, are you singing or not?
Come on, take the drums''

528
00:54:00,303 --> 00:54:03,466
The queen mother's orders.
- Play the trumpets

529
00:54:05,141 --> 00:54:09,373
''lf l curse you, you'll end up with
blind and deaf husbands''

530
00:54:12,148 --> 00:54:14,810
Come on.
- You must sit with me

531
00:54:16,553 --> 00:54:20,546
Was yours a love marriage too?
- ls yours a love marriage?

532
00:54:21,825 --> 00:54:24,953
Not entirely. Fifty-fifty.
- What do you mean?

533
00:54:26,162 --> 00:54:30,098
We were in college together.
We started liking each other

534
00:54:30,967 --> 00:54:33,834
''The families got to know,
an alliance was talked about''

535
00:54:33,970 --> 00:54:35,904
''And today, l'm getting married.
- Are you glad?''

536
00:54:36,106 --> 00:54:42,534
''Elated! What more does a girl want?
A good husband, a nice home''

537
00:54:43,113 --> 00:54:46,207
And a lovely child.
- Just one child?

538
00:54:48,051 --> 00:54:50,576
''You too are glad, aren't you
about becoming a mother?''

539
00:54:52,122 --> 00:54:55,023
''Your husband must be
loving you dearly, no?''

540
00:55:09,372 --> 00:55:14,571
''lf you wanted me to become
a stranger to you...''

541
00:55:15,145 --> 00:55:22,142
''tell me Mother, why did you
endear me so?''

542
00:56:08,865 --> 00:56:10,594
''Henna on my hands''

543
00:56:12,435 --> 00:56:14,426
''The dot on my forehead''

544
00:56:16,373 --> 00:56:18,136
''l've hennaed my hands''

545
00:56:18,308 --> 00:56:19,866
''l'm wearing a dot''

546
00:56:20,043 --> 00:56:21,874
''My bangles are chiming''

547
00:56:22,045 --> 00:56:23,740
''My anklets are clinking''

548
00:56:25,148 --> 00:56:29,141
''l want to sing the song of love''

549
00:56:36,459 --> 00:56:39,895
''l want to go
to my beloved's house''

550
00:56:40,096 --> 00:56:43,497
''Yes, l want to go
to my beloved's house''

551
00:57:03,720 --> 00:57:07,383
''At birth to our parents...''

552
00:57:07,657 --> 00:57:10,990
''we are estranged''

553
00:57:11,294 --> 00:57:13,990
''Oh what fate is the daughter's''

554
00:57:37,353 --> 00:57:40,880
''ln a moment, l'll sever
all relationships''

555
00:57:41,090 --> 00:57:44,423
''l'm leaving my father's house''

556
00:57:48,331 --> 00:57:55,100
''The rest of my life l'll spend
in the land of my beloved''

557
00:57:55,338 --> 00:57:58,899
''l'm leaving for
my beloved's house''

558
00:57:59,108 --> 00:58:02,509
''Yes, l'm leaving for
to my beloved's house''

559
00:58:26,269 --> 00:58:29,898
''But it's a daughter's destiny...''

560
00:58:30,039 --> 00:58:32,940
''that makes them weep''

561
00:58:33,309 --> 00:58:40,147
''The child they bore will be
borne away by someone''

562
00:58:47,991 --> 00:58:51,483
''l'm leaving for
my beloved's house''

563
00:58:51,694 --> 00:58:55,357
''Yes, l'm leaving for
to my beloved's house''

564
00:59:01,804 --> 00:59:04,329
What would've happened had l eaten
an entire biscuit?

565
00:59:04,641 --> 00:59:07,337
He wants biscuits! Would you
like some biscuits?

566
00:59:07,610 --> 00:59:11,512
You'll feed me biscuits?!
Scoundrel!

567
00:59:14,183 --> 00:59:20,782
Let go! Why are you fighting?
- l was trying to be of help

568
00:59:20,957 --> 00:59:23,517
l offered him biscuits.
- Not biscuits again!

569
00:59:25,528 --> 00:59:28,725
No mentioning biscuits!
- No mention

570
00:59:29,866 --> 00:59:32,460
''Mr Gulabchand, why are so worked up
over biscuits?''

571
00:59:32,635 --> 00:59:37,937
''This evening, while
l was locking up my shop...''

572
00:59:38,141 --> 00:59:42,942
''in walks a boy who looks like
a filmi hero, and he says...''

573
00:59:43,046 --> 00:59:46,948
''he's Dewanchand's man.
Maybe l said, and l said...''

574
00:59:47,150 --> 00:59:48,742
Come in. Sit

575
00:59:48,885 --> 00:59:51,752
Show me the necklace.
How much do you need?

576
00:59:52,055 --> 00:59:57,049
''50,000 or so.
- This belongs to Dewanchand''

577
00:59:57,293 --> 00:59:59,158
Have a biscuit.
- Biscuit...?

578
00:59:59,295 --> 01:00:01,160
lt's his too.
- He makes biscuits too?

579
01:00:01,331 --> 01:00:02,662
Yes

580
01:00:03,166 --> 01:00:04,428
Eat

581
01:00:08,171 --> 01:00:10,162
Tasty.
- lt is...?

582
01:00:18,815 --> 01:00:26,187
''When l came around, l saw my safe
flung open, cleaned of 50,000''

583
01:00:27,190 --> 01:00:29,181
And the necklace?
- lt was a fake

584
01:00:29,292 --> 01:00:32,386
But this biscuit is real.
That's why l assaulted him

585
01:00:32,595 --> 01:00:39,831
l'm going to make mincemeat of you!
- Bridespeople ought to be humble

586
01:00:39,969 --> 01:00:42,460
What bridespeople?
- We're the bridespeople

587
01:00:43,272 --> 01:00:49,472
''Oh yes, hit me.
- l feel like it, but l won't''

588
01:00:49,646 --> 01:00:52,638
Hit me!
- We're the bridespeople

589
01:00:52,749 --> 01:00:55,946
l'll spare you.
- You hit me! Or l hit you

590
01:00:59,155 --> 01:01:01,146
What happened?

591
01:01:01,424 --> 01:01:02,948
What's the problem?

592
01:01:05,161 --> 01:01:06,822
Him...

593
01:01:07,163 --> 01:01:09,154
''He's the biscuit-wallah,
the scoundrel!''

594
01:01:12,435 --> 01:01:14,426
Where did he go?

595
01:01:15,772 --> 01:01:18,172
What happened Mr Gulabchand?
- Have you seen the biscuit-wallah?

596
01:01:18,408 --> 01:01:20,399
You'd like some biscuits?
- No

597
01:01:21,077 --> 01:01:24,376
No biscuits! Biscuit-wallah! Police!

598
01:01:31,120 --> 01:01:34,351
Where's the biscuit-wallah?

599
01:01:34,524 --> 01:01:36,856
Found it!
- Where?

600
01:01:37,126 --> 01:01:40,118
''Got myself a sweet.
- No, the biscuit-wallah''

601
01:01:42,131 --> 01:01:43,598
Must be upstairs

602
01:01:46,135 --> 01:01:48,126
Where is he... where?

603
01:02:03,052 --> 01:02:06,146
Don't scream. l'm a thief.
But you needn't be afraid

604
01:02:06,589 --> 01:02:11,492
''l needed 50,000 to buy ajob in Dubai.
So l robbed a moneylender''

605
01:02:11,594 --> 01:02:14,154
Knocked him out with a laced biscuit.
But bad-luck's very bad

606
01:02:14,330 --> 01:02:19,495
And he's right here with the police.
l'll leave once he's gone

607
01:02:19,702 --> 01:02:21,431
l hope you aren't afraid anymore

608
01:02:21,704 --> 01:02:24,639
Blink if you mean yes.
Promise me not to scream

609
01:02:31,848 --> 01:02:33,372
l'll be out in a while

610
01:02:37,120 --> 01:02:39,111
Gulshan... you?
- Yes Maithili

611
01:02:40,456 --> 01:02:42,447
What are you doing?
- What l am doing?

612
01:02:43,126 --> 01:02:48,655
''What have you done Maithili, and why?
- What have l done?''

613
01:02:49,232 --> 01:02:58,334
''Maithili, you broke my heart! l failed
college thrice, just to be with you''

614
01:02:58,674 --> 01:03:01,609
''And today, you marry Atul?
- What nonsense is this?''

615
01:03:01,878 --> 01:03:08,147
''Actually Maithili, l love you.
l've always loved you''

616
01:03:08,417 --> 01:03:12,410
And today l'm marrying you.
- Get out this moment!

617
01:03:12,522 --> 01:03:16,959
''Else, l'll scream!
- Call everyone, the whole world...''

618
01:03:17,059 --> 01:03:19,152
for me to bare my soul
before everyone

619
01:03:19,428 --> 01:03:23,626
Only one goddess reigns
in my heart. Maithili

620
01:03:27,170 --> 01:03:32,107
My friend! We've met.
But what are you doing here?

621
01:03:33,109 --> 01:03:38,103
l went to fetch biscuit for you.
You haven't had a bite all day

622
01:03:38,447 --> 01:03:40,108
Eat a biscuit

623
01:03:44,120 --> 01:03:45,314
Tasty

624
01:03:45,454 --> 01:03:47,115
One for my wife

625
01:03:50,560 --> 01:03:51,754
Cost-effective. Reliable

626
01:03:51,828 --> 01:03:54,558
By the time you're halfway through
you're asleep. My Biscuit Number One

627
01:03:58,134 --> 01:04:02,127
There were no other options.
- But what do we do with him now?

628
01:04:02,805 --> 01:04:04,796
What will folks say
if they get to know...

629
01:04:04,907 --> 01:04:07,307
''that there are two men with me,
one standing, one in bed...?''

630
01:04:08,477 --> 01:04:13,141
First let's take care of the man
in bed. Let's take care of you

631
01:04:21,591 --> 01:04:25,152
He's taking a comfortable ride
in civic waste

632
01:04:25,428 --> 01:04:27,020
l'll be on my way.
- One minute...

633
01:04:27,163 --> 01:04:29,154
What happened?
- Let me see if anyone's around

634
01:04:35,905 --> 01:04:39,102
They're picketing right outside.
- Then where to go?

635
01:04:40,109 --> 01:04:42,009
Wait here for a while
- You won't scream?

636
01:04:42,111 --> 01:04:43,100
No

637
01:04:50,119 --> 01:04:54,954
''Get me paper, pen and an envelope.
- For writing?''

638
01:04:55,124 --> 01:04:56,614
To eat

639
01:04:58,294 --> 01:05:02,390
What are you saying?
No! Don't say that! Not at this time

640
01:05:03,933 --> 01:05:06,527
What happened?
- Deven just refused me

641
01:05:08,404 --> 01:05:12,135
He was my last hope!
My heart is sinking

642
01:05:15,478 --> 01:05:18,470
''Time l left, Vaidehi''

643
01:05:19,916 --> 01:05:23,477
''Want me to drop you somewhere?
Where will you go, what will you do?''

644
01:05:23,653 --> 01:05:26,645
''Haven't given it a thought, am l right?
- Yes...''

645
01:05:27,256 --> 01:05:29,884
''Will you do something for me?
- Sure, tell me''

646
01:05:30,426 --> 01:05:35,090
My mother lives in Haripur.
Deliver this envelope to her

647
01:05:36,098 --> 01:05:38,430
''lt contains offerings to God,
and a letter addressed to her''

648
01:05:39,101 --> 01:05:42,901
''And here, keep some money.
- No, l don't need money''

649
01:05:43,105 --> 01:05:45,403
lt'll be useful for the trip.
lf you don't spend it...

650
01:05:45,508 --> 01:05:47,703
''give it to my mother,
and tell her l'm fine''

651
01:05:48,210 --> 01:05:51,111
The name and address are
on the envelope. One more thing

652
01:05:52,114 --> 01:05:53,911
Don't forget to eat coconut

653
01:05:55,451 --> 01:05:57,351
Where are you taking me?
- On moment...

654
01:05:57,453 --> 01:06:00,115
''Tell me, what's the matter?
- Will you step inside please?''

655
01:06:00,389 --> 01:06:02,118
Say it right here

656
01:06:04,460 --> 01:06:09,124
Here's your money?
- All of it?

657
01:06:11,133 --> 01:06:16,127
''You see, some extra expenses...''

658
01:06:17,139 --> 01:06:19,004
''there's a shortfall of 50,000''

659
01:06:19,475 --> 01:06:23,138
l've telephoned a friend.
He'll give it before the wedding

660
01:06:24,146 --> 01:06:28,139
''lf he doesn't, l'll deliver the money
to you personally in two days. l swear''

661
01:06:28,484 --> 01:06:33,421
Let the wedding happen after two days.
- No! Please don't do that

662
01:06:35,091 --> 01:06:39,425
This is a matter of my honour!
lt's going to kill me

663
01:06:40,096 --> 01:06:44,260
''l've said it so many times,
now l tell you for the last time''

664
01:06:45,434 --> 01:06:48,096
Five minutes before the bridegroom
sits down for the wedding...

665
01:06:48,237 --> 01:06:52,230
the entire money must be in my hands.
Else we're walking out

666
01:06:52,441 --> 01:06:55,433
l understand.
- How much?

667
01:06:56,112 --> 01:06:58,103
500000
- ln...?

668
01:06:58,280 --> 01:07:00,908
Cash.
- ln wads of...?

669
01:07:01,117 --> 01:07:02,914
Five hundreds

670
01:07:24,874 --> 01:07:26,865
''l'll be leaving now, Vaidehi.
- But what happens now?''

671
01:07:27,643 --> 01:07:29,577
''How will he get 50,000?''

672
01:07:31,080 --> 01:07:32,877
Why are you staring at me?

673
01:07:35,484 --> 01:07:39,580
''You expect me to give up 50,000?
l can't do it! Question doesn't arise''

674
01:07:41,090 --> 01:07:45,493
He was saying he'll pay up in two days.
- By then someone else will have my job

675
01:07:45,961 --> 01:07:49,488
l committed this robbery for the job.
You want me to thieve all my life?

676
01:07:51,534 --> 01:07:54,799
Maithili's wedding is at stake. Think!
- Why should l think?

677
01:07:55,104 --> 01:07:58,665
And why are you thinking? We walked
in here to evade the police

678
01:07:59,108 --> 01:08:03,101
Doesn't make us their family members.
l belong to none of them. Farewell

679
01:08:25,134 --> 01:08:27,466
''Maithili, hush''

680
01:08:29,138 --> 01:08:34,474
l think there's only one option.
- l can't bear to see...

681
01:08:34,577 --> 01:08:38,479
my father being humiliated like this.
- What kind of a boy is Atul?

682
01:08:39,148 --> 01:08:40,877
He's nice

683
01:08:41,150 --> 01:08:44,381
He loves you?
- Yes

684
01:08:45,020 --> 01:08:48,751
''Then talk to him. lf he talks reason,
his father will surely agree''

685
01:08:57,166 --> 01:08:59,691
Come in Atul.
- You wanted to see me?

686
01:08:59,935 --> 01:09:01,163
Sit

687
01:09:04,340 --> 01:09:06,171
''What is the matter, Maithili?''

688
01:09:08,177 --> 01:09:11,578
There's a small problem.
l'm apprehensive about telling you

689
01:09:12,181 --> 01:09:16,641
''Apprehensive about telling me?
ln a while, we'll be married''

690
01:09:17,186 --> 01:09:22,180
''We're going to become life partners.
lf not me, whom will you tell?''

691
01:09:25,060 --> 01:09:28,188
''You've taken a burden off my mind.
- Tell me, what is the problem?''

692
01:09:29,098 --> 01:09:33,933
Papa has provided for whatever
your father demanded for the wedding

693
01:09:34,136 --> 01:09:37,333
''Yes, l've seen. He has given
each and every thing''

694
01:09:38,374 --> 01:09:41,138
Only one thing is lacking.
- What's lacking?

695
01:09:42,211 --> 01:09:46,147
''He had demanded 500,000.
450,000 has been organised''

696
01:09:47,149 --> 01:09:51,142
''There's a shortfall of 50,000.
My father wants a 2-day grace''

697
01:09:51,387 --> 01:09:53,378
But your father refuses to agree.

698
01:09:54,156 --> 01:09:56,147
You are the only one who
can reason with him.

699
01:09:57,293 --> 01:09:59,818
''This is a huge problem, Maithili''

700
01:10:03,465 --> 01:10:09,165
''Where's the problem? Papa isn't
refusing. Look, he's suffering from...''

701
01:10:09,271 --> 01:10:12,729
blood pressure. So much tension is no
good for him. He's asking for 2 days

702
01:10:12,841 --> 01:10:17,039
''Not a question of 2 days or 4 days,
it's a matter of principles''

703
01:10:17,246 --> 01:10:21,114
''lf your father has promised to pay
500,000 today, he ought to pay up''

704
01:10:21,917 --> 01:10:26,980
''And in our family, it's a tradition.
The elders decide the give-and-take''

705
01:10:27,189 --> 01:10:33,128
''Youngsters have no say in the matter,
and l advise you not to say anything''

706
01:10:33,295 --> 01:10:38,790
Leave everything to your father.
l'm sure he will find the money

707
01:10:39,134 --> 01:10:40,999
l should be leaving

708
01:10:42,137 --> 01:10:46,801
''And yes, l've finalised our honeymoon
in Mauritius. Everything will be fine''

709
01:10:50,045 --> 01:10:51,478
Bye

710
01:11:02,891 --> 01:11:05,883
''Have you brought the money?
- All of 50,000. Count it''

711
01:11:06,495 --> 01:11:08,895
''l trust you, l do''

712
01:11:11,166 --> 01:11:14,567
Sign these papers

713
01:11:16,005 --> 01:11:17,836
You got a pen?

714
01:11:18,173 --> 01:11:20,164
You got a pen right there

715
01:11:29,785 --> 01:11:34,279
''You're beautiful too.
- Writes lovely, it's my lucky pen''

716
01:11:35,457 --> 01:11:37,357
''Pen, change my luck''

717
01:11:37,559 --> 01:11:40,926
Hurry up. We got to set out
for Bombay in an hour

718
01:11:42,665 --> 01:11:44,530
Now you're settled in life

719
01:11:44,767 --> 01:11:48,134
Leave the bottle. Out with the cash.
- Bitch! You've been after me...

720
01:11:48,237 --> 01:11:51,638
''for an hour! Get lost, get laid.
- l'm not leaving without my money''

721
01:11:51,840 --> 01:11:53,831
You bargain for one man
and you bring in four over

722
01:11:54,043 --> 01:11:55,874
And you can't pay for it?
Out with the cash

723
01:11:56,045 --> 01:11:59,378
Teaching me how to count?
Take what you've got and get lost

724
01:11:59,481 --> 01:12:02,473
Or l'll snatch it away. Get lost.
- Snatch it? Like it's yours?

725
01:12:05,154 --> 01:12:08,817
You know who l am?
l'll haul you in

726
01:12:09,491 --> 01:12:11,823
You're a policeman. How can you
take sides with them?

727
01:12:12,161 --> 01:12:15,062
''l left nothing undone to please you,
and when it comes to money...''

728
01:12:15,164 --> 01:12:17,325
''you'll shortchange a poor girl?
Come on, let me have my money''

729
01:12:17,499 --> 01:12:19,831
Just sign it. lt's routine here.
You want to take the flight or not?

730
01:12:19,968 --> 01:12:22,562
l want it right now.
- l can't pay you right now

731
01:12:22,738 --> 01:12:24,467
Why not?
- You want to get thrashed?

732
01:12:24,540 --> 01:12:26,838
l'm not going unless
l'm given my money

733
01:12:27,076 --> 01:12:29,704
What will you do with
so much money? Marry?

734
01:12:29,878 --> 01:12:35,441
''No such luck, question being the same.
Money. What man marries without money?''

735
01:12:36,385 --> 01:12:40,116
A poor girl has only two choices.
Poison yourself or get into the trade

736
01:12:40,389 --> 01:12:44,120
''l'm doing this filthy job for my
sister's wedding, for her dowry''

737
01:12:44,626 --> 01:12:49,928
Please let me have my money.
- First bring your sister here

738
01:12:50,132 --> 01:12:53,329
''l'll pay you double rate.
- Why not your sister, you pimp?''

739
01:13:10,152 --> 01:13:14,145
''You'll pay her. All of it.
- Who are you, brother?''

740
01:13:14,323 --> 01:13:17,554
''Whoever l may be, you will
pay her right now''

741
01:13:17,726 --> 01:13:21,025
l take care of her bookings.
Let me know if you need

742
01:13:23,198 --> 01:13:24,961
''Hey, you don't know me?''

743
01:14:11,947 --> 01:14:13,938
Clean out your pockets.
Give her the money

744
01:14:17,052 --> 01:14:19,043
That chain too.
- lt's mine

745
01:14:21,423 --> 01:14:24,483
Go back to your village.
- Thank you

746
01:14:26,628 --> 01:14:29,927
''Listen, where are you off with the cash?
You won't find anotherjob like this''

747
01:14:30,098 --> 01:14:31,497
Excuse me...

748
01:14:32,100 --> 01:14:34,660
Looks like he's looking for someone
too. And he's more worked up than l am

749
01:14:36,004 --> 01:14:39,997
''Excuse me, l'm looking for this woman.
- l'm out of this business''

750
01:14:40,542 --> 01:14:44,376
Helping someone isn't bad business.
lt's a pious deed

751
01:14:44,546 --> 01:14:47,106
Enough of piety for me.
l'm going to wash my sins

752
01:14:47,316 --> 01:14:51,252
''l'm a troubled man, l've been troubled
all day. l must find this woman''

753
01:14:51,386 --> 01:14:53,377
Don't talk of another woman

754
01:14:55,123 --> 01:14:58,786
Help! Police!
- A policeman is beating you up

755
01:14:59,127 --> 01:15:01,118
Goodness!

756
01:15:01,463 --> 01:15:06,457
Robbers! Goons! Mafia! Underworld!
Brothers! Help!

757
01:15:10,572 --> 01:15:14,133
We saw her getting off a truck at the
checkpost. After that we lost her

758
01:15:16,812 --> 01:15:19,144
What did you do next?
- We informed the police

759
01:15:19,281 --> 01:15:22,648
''They're combing the city.
Railway stations, bus stands, everywhere''

760
01:15:23,619 --> 01:15:29,251
Waiting for you beside a phone booth
near Rani Laxmibai Hall

761
01:15:29,558 --> 01:15:31,082
Stay there. l'm coming

762
01:15:44,106 --> 01:15:46,768
Where's Mr Hazarilal?
- There. Seated

763
01:15:50,846 --> 01:15:53,110
Where are you going?
- Nowhere

764
01:15:53,448 --> 01:15:55,916
Yourjewellery?
- None of your concern

765
01:15:56,919 --> 01:15:58,614
You aren't giving yourjewellery
away to Hazarilal

766
01:15:58,787 --> 01:16:00,778
Who are you to stop me?

767
01:16:02,124 --> 01:16:03,648
Tubelight

768
01:16:04,526 --> 01:16:08,622
''Yes, tubelight. Takes me
a while longer to understand''

769
01:16:09,131 --> 01:16:11,122
This time l took
a little longer to light up

770
01:16:12,134 --> 01:16:15,126
And yourjob?
- You want the wedding to happen?

771
01:16:16,138 --> 01:16:20,541
l want the same. Wear yourjewellery.
l'll give the money to Nekchand

772
01:16:22,010 --> 01:16:23,477
What would you like?

773
01:16:25,480 --> 01:16:29,041
Forgive me.
- Forgive you? l'm the one...

774
01:16:29,151 --> 01:16:31,085
who ought to apologise.
- But the mistake was mine

775
01:16:31,253 --> 01:16:34,416
''lrrespective, the bridespeople
are the ones who have to apologise''

776
01:16:34,623 --> 01:16:37,922
''That's the rule, we apologise until
the bride has been sent off''

777
01:16:38,093 --> 01:16:39,890
''Until the send-off,
we'll be grovelling''

778
01:16:40,095 --> 01:16:42,825
l'm one of the bridespeople too.
- You too?

779
01:16:43,231 --> 01:16:45,756
''l regret meeting you,
but who are you?''

780
01:16:46,101 --> 01:16:49,366
l'm Bansidhar's son.
- Who's Bansidhar?

781
01:16:49,538 --> 01:16:52,098
The flour miller.
- Bansidhar the miller?

782
01:16:52,341 --> 01:16:54,332
''l'm the one,
the one and only''

783
01:17:01,516 --> 01:17:08,285
Nice meeting. How is your son?
- My son is a disgrace

784
01:17:08,523 --> 01:17:12,289
''He married a girl he wanted,
and he's gone. lf l find him...''

785
01:17:12,461 --> 01:17:15,123
l'll put him through my grindmill!
- Do that. Bye

786
01:17:15,464 --> 01:17:18,126
Where are you going? Who are you?
- l'm Bansidhar's father

787
01:17:18,400 --> 01:17:21,733
''Now son, now father?
Goodness! Who are you?''

788
01:17:22,037 --> 01:17:25,473
What goes on between father and son?
- l'm in a maze! Who am l?

789
01:17:25,607 --> 01:17:28,007
Who are you? Who is he?
- Look Bansidhar...

790
01:17:28,143 --> 01:17:32,341
your son is back home.
He isn't a prodigal

791
01:17:32,614 --> 01:17:34,878
What else do you call him?
- You explain that to him

792
01:17:35,083 --> 01:17:38,883
''Let me go and fetch my wife, Daddy.
- Daddy...? Wife...?''

793
01:17:39,087 --> 01:17:41,078
l've met your daughter-in-law.
She's very nice

794
01:17:41,256 --> 01:17:44,089
He isn't my son! So much for my
daughter-in-law. Who are you?

795
01:17:44,393 --> 01:17:46,384
Have you met Mr Nekchand?
- l'm in trouble

796
01:17:46,561 --> 01:17:48,552
What happened?
- Happened to meet my father

797
01:17:48,697 --> 01:17:50,096
''Father...?
- Yes, Bansidhar''

798
01:17:50,298 --> 01:17:53,096
''Luckily Mr Nekchand barged in.
Else, l would've been exposed''

799
01:17:53,268 --> 01:17:55,259
Stop looking in that direction.
Come on

800
01:17:56,438 --> 01:17:58,429
Whatever you can let me have
will be of great help

801
01:17:59,441 --> 01:18:02,433
''l'll be obliged to you.
Whatever you can, please''

802
01:18:04,446 --> 01:18:06,107
''Forgive me my child,
what is the matter?''

803
01:18:06,281 --> 01:18:09,114
''Uncle, l'd like to speak to you.
- Yes, my child?''

804
01:18:11,119 --> 01:18:14,987
l noticed something...
- l'm so confused about the wedding

805
01:18:15,123 --> 01:18:16,988
l can't make out anything...

806
01:18:25,467 --> 01:18:28,459
l just wanted to tell you that
l've never seen such a grand wedding

807
01:18:30,706 --> 01:18:35,871
''No, you're saying that to please me.
- No uncle, really''

808
01:18:36,278 --> 01:18:39,941
''You've taken care of everything,
right down to the smallest detail''

809
01:18:40,248 --> 01:18:42,478
''Great food, great...''

810
01:18:43,819 --> 01:18:45,810
''What happened, uncle?''

811
01:18:49,057 --> 01:18:51,389
The first words of appreciation
ever since...

812
01:18:51,493 --> 01:18:59,161
''l set out organising this wedding.
Else, everyone has been...''

813
01:19:01,536 --> 01:19:05,165
Why only me? Every parent
starts preparing for this day...

814
01:19:05,273 --> 01:19:11,974
''as soon as his daughter is born.
This decor, all this arrangement...''

815
01:19:12,180 --> 01:19:18,176
wasn't done in four days. lt's a dream
l built moment by moment...

816
01:19:18,353 --> 01:19:26,920
as l watched Maithili grow up.
l wouldn't leave anything lacking

817
01:19:27,596 --> 01:19:30,793
''l'd give her everything,
and l've given her everything''

818
01:19:31,566 --> 01:19:40,372
All except this... you see this doll?
l bought it for her...

819
01:19:40,475 --> 01:19:45,310
when Maithili was three.
She looked exactly like it

820
01:19:46,648 --> 01:19:54,316
''For me, she's still the same.
And this is all l'm keeping''

821
01:19:55,157 --> 01:19:57,148
lt's all l'll be left with

822
01:20:02,164 --> 01:20:06,658
''Mr Nekchand, it's time. Come.
- Please proceed. We'll join you''

823
01:20:08,170 --> 01:20:11,833
''Come on, take the bag.
- The entire money isn't there''

824
01:20:12,073 --> 01:20:14,837
Everything will work out fine.
Come along. Come

825
01:20:18,382 --> 01:20:19,713
Only then will the
wedding take place.

826
01:20:19,883 --> 01:20:22,374
May l sit in the mandap?
- Not yet the right time..

827
01:20:23,053 --> 01:20:24,384
lt's come.

828
01:20:24,788 --> 01:20:27,154
Give it to him.
- You took your own time.

829
01:20:28,392 --> 01:20:29,723
This..

830
01:20:30,127 --> 01:20:31,389
Total?

831
01:20:32,396 --> 01:20:34,057
Yes...no...

832
01:20:36,400 --> 01:20:40,393
l tried my level best..
- No problem.

833
01:20:40,737 --> 01:20:43,001
We're not stone-hearted.

834
01:20:43,407 --> 01:20:47,070
They may not be 500 notes
but the money is all there.

835
01:20:47,744 --> 01:20:49,336
''Priest, start the chants.''

836
01:20:51,081 --> 01:20:52,343
Sit down.

837
01:21:29,386 --> 01:21:31,377
Sit with your beloved.

838
01:21:40,063 --> 01:21:41,394
Count the notes in this bag.
Should be Rs. 500000.

839
01:21:42,399 --> 01:21:44,890
The bank bundles too
have missing notes.

840
01:21:47,337 --> 01:21:48,668
Happy?

841
01:21:54,344 --> 01:21:57,074
Found it! l've found my money!

842
01:21:57,681 --> 01:21:59,774
Found your stolen money?
- Yes! - Where?

843
01:21:59,950 --> 01:22:02,009
ln the bag.
- My bag?

844
01:22:02,352 --> 01:22:03,683
That's my money.

845
01:22:04,354 --> 01:22:07,084
Your Rs. 450000 is in the bag.

846
01:22:07,357 --> 01:22:09,086
But these 5 bundles
of Rs. 100 are mine.

847
01:22:09,359 --> 01:22:13,352
How do you know?
- The note had vermilion.

848
01:22:13,764 --> 01:22:15,356
Do you see it or not?

849
01:22:15,432 --> 01:22:17,366
Yes..
- Then it is mine!

850
01:22:18,035 --> 01:22:20,868
Thank you. Here's your bag.
- Just a minute.

851
01:22:21,104 --> 01:22:23,095
Now what? - Nekchand!
- He's calling you.

852
01:22:25,375 --> 01:22:27,366
He's calling you.
- Excuse me!

853
01:22:29,379 --> 01:22:32,871
Forgive me.
- Forgiveness comes later.

854
01:22:33,383 --> 01:22:35,647
''First tell me, the
500000 that you gave me..''

855
01:22:35,986 --> 01:22:38,181
He says 50000 in it is his.

856
01:22:38,388 --> 01:22:40,049
l only gave 450000.

857
01:22:41,391 --> 01:22:42,881
Drama..?

858
01:22:44,394 --> 01:22:47,329
Rs. 50000 was in this bag.
Stolen money.

859
01:22:47,664 --> 01:22:49,791
They are not mine.
l know nothing about it.

860
01:22:50,333 --> 01:22:52,130
We'll know soon enough.
Priest stop the ceremony.

861
01:22:52,335 --> 01:22:54,326
No..
- Why did they stop the chants..?

862
01:22:56,339 --> 01:22:57,738
Son Atul...

863
01:22:58,008 --> 01:22:59,339
Get up.

864
01:23:00,343 --> 01:23:02,675
Don't do this.
Don't stop the marriage.

865
01:23:03,346 --> 01:23:05,678
This matter will be solved.
- lt's got more complicated.

866
01:23:06,750 --> 01:23:09,344
Till we find out where
the stolen money came from..

867
01:23:09,619 --> 01:23:10,950
This marriage won't take place.

868
01:23:11,354 --> 01:23:15,085
Also tell us where the
remaining 450000 came from.

869
01:23:17,360 --> 01:23:19,123
My lodging and boarding
for 6 months has been fixed.

870
01:23:19,696 --> 01:23:21,186
Time to go to jail.

871
01:23:21,364 --> 01:23:22,854
Do meet mother.

872
01:23:23,366 --> 01:23:26,164
l swear by my daughter...

873
01:23:28,038 --> 01:23:31,371
l pawned everything l
owned to collect this sum.

874
01:23:32,375 --> 01:23:35,367
l know nothing about the 50000.

875
01:23:35,712 --> 01:23:37,703
You are lying!
- He is speaking the truth.

876
01:23:38,381 --> 01:23:39,814
l kept the money in the bag.

877
01:23:40,717 --> 01:23:43,151
Who is he? - Who knows?
- How did he come here?

878
01:23:43,720 --> 01:23:46,052
Found him! He's the
one with the biscuit!

879
01:23:46,389 --> 01:23:48,323
Are you Bansidhar's son?

880
01:23:50,060 --> 01:23:51,652
l am nobody's son.

881
01:23:51,995 --> 01:23:53,326
l am a thief.

882
01:23:55,065 --> 01:23:58,330
l stole his money and gate crashed
into this wedding to escape the cops.

883
01:24:01,338 --> 01:24:05,001
''l come here to see that in the name
of customs, respected people of...''

884
01:24:05,342 --> 01:24:09,005
..society fleece the vulnerable
father of this innocent girl.

885
01:24:10,347 --> 01:24:11,780
l thought of helping them.

886
01:24:12,015 --> 01:24:13,346
He was short of 50000 in the dowry.

887
01:24:14,017 --> 01:24:17,009
l placed my loot in his bag.
He knows nothing about it.

888
01:24:17,354 --> 01:24:20,346
Enough! We've seen this
stale story in many films.

889
01:24:20,857 --> 01:24:22,188
Tell us the truth!

890
01:24:22,359 --> 01:24:24,691
''Uncle, l'll tell the truth.''

891
01:24:25,962 --> 01:24:27,953
He's having an affair with Maithili!

892
01:24:28,098 --> 01:24:29,360
What nonsense!

893
01:24:29,699 --> 01:24:32,167
l saw it myself!
He was in her room.

894
01:24:32,369 --> 01:24:34,360
They have a thing going!

895
01:24:35,372 --> 01:24:37,363
One more word and l'll..!

896
01:24:38,375 --> 01:24:40,104
One minute...

897
01:24:40,777 --> 01:24:43,803
How did you know this thief
has something on with her?

898
01:24:44,381 --> 01:24:46,645
l saw it myself.
- Listen..

899
01:24:47,050 --> 01:24:49,041
He was in Maithili's room.

900
01:24:50,320 --> 01:24:51,981
A stranger in the bride's room!

901
01:24:52,322 --> 01:24:54,813
For a whole hour!
- Listen to that!

902
01:24:55,325 --> 01:24:56,815
And the door was shut.

903
01:24:57,060 --> 01:24:58,823
Now what can one say?
- lts a lie!

904
01:24:59,329 --> 01:25:01,092
He is lying! Accusing!

905
01:25:01,331 --> 01:25:02,821
May maggots crawl over you!

906
01:25:03,066 --> 01:25:04,328
Ask the thief if l'm lying!

907
01:25:05,335 --> 01:25:07,326
Why ask the thief?
Ask this girl!

908
01:25:10,340 --> 01:25:12,331
So? ls Gulu speaking the truth?

909
01:25:12,843 --> 01:25:14,834
Was the thief in your
room for a whole hour?

910
01:25:17,347 --> 01:25:19,076
What..are you saying?

911
01:25:19,749 --> 01:25:21,341
Now what do you say?

912
01:25:21,852 --> 01:25:24,343
Why are you bent on
reviling my little honour?

913
01:25:24,688 --> 01:25:27,020
You have no honour left.
Lost it all.

914
01:25:27,357 --> 01:25:29,348
Down the drain!
- That's enough.

915
01:25:30,360 --> 01:25:32,828
Maligning a truthful girl
without knowing the truth!

916
01:25:34,364 --> 01:25:37,356
l hid in her room
to escape Gulabchand.

917
01:25:39,035 --> 01:25:40,366
l had no clue it was the bride's room.

918
01:25:41,371 --> 01:25:43,362
''Before this day, she had
never set eyes on me!''

919
01:25:43,707 --> 01:25:45,834
The poor thing doesn't
even know my name!

920
01:25:49,312 --> 01:25:53,043
Maithili is a girl of good character.

921
01:25:54,651 --> 01:25:56,642
l beg you with folded hands..

922
01:25:57,320 --> 01:25:58,651
